\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4151349\charrsid7427796 Yes.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4151349\charrsid7427796 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri113\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin113\lin1871\itap0\pararsid6571465 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid6571465\charrsid6571465 Harry:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4151349\charrsid7427796 Well, it\rquote s the idea that \endash  and I learnt this much later on \endash  that it\rquote s an Ashanti practice in West Africa, that where you\rquote 
re born, the umbilical cord, when you are born, is cut off, and a piece of it is kept in the room until you\rquote re old enough to understand what it is - well, not that I understood what it really was (LAUGHS), and it\rquote s explained that it\rquote 
s part of you, and then it\rquote s buried into the ground, and the tree is planted on it, and that is your link with that spot, and with that tree, and it\rquote s your responsibility.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4151349\charrsid7427796 
