t been to those parts, though I still have a number of cousins, direct blood relatives, in the area.  But as I said, my sister sold the land, and we didn\rquote t forgive her for that, because we just felt it should be kept.  She didn\rquote 
t need the money.  So that\rquote s the idea, that it should be always there.  What would have happened had she not sold it, relatives who were there would just have squatted on it, and it passes into mythology.  So that\rquote 
