int about that, in terms of religious consciousness and my parents, my relationship with my mother, was that she was very distraught when I decided to abandon that side of life, even though I stressed that I still had an interest in religion, but not as a
 worshipper as such, but I wanted to be a theologian.  I was very well read amongst the people like Robinson, you remember Robinson, Bishop of Woolwich?  My Headmaster introduced me to him}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
