ter, and again, because of my interest in religion, he introduced me to her\'85
. I met them frequently, and discussions.  Then I was very influenced by my history teacher, who saw my interest in things, and introduced me to writers like Paul Tillich, the theo
logian, and Bonhofer and so on.  So by the time I left school, I was pretty well grounded in theological thinking.  And I went to Lancaster, in fact, I was encouraged to go to Lancaster to do theology and philosophy \endash  which is what I went to do 
