\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4151349\charrsid7427796 Similarly, yeah.  Again, he\rquote s from the same background, indeed, they\rquote re cousins, because his mother is a sister of my father\rquote s \endash 
 which is the only example I know of, in the Caribbean stories \endash  of such proximity.  And I remember he raised this with my parents and said, \'93Is that allowed?\'94  And they said,  "Yes".  When they were younger, them used to know so
me similar situations.  So in terms of family network, they were fairly close.  And she returned with my parents.  Now, I was going to explain this complex situation which you\rquote ll find in your Jamaican families \endash 
 that I have two further brothers, elderly brothers, if you like, in that my sister was born \endash  Ann \endash  and then, soon after she was born, my father had a son \endash  not with my mother \endash 
 but with another woman.  And that son [Fonso], that child, was brought up by the same uncle, Uncle Charles, whom I\rquote ve mentioned.  And then, within my father\rquote 
s family, came another brother, George.  So you look at it this way.  My sister, and then just a bit younger is this brother from outside, and then just across here is my second brother.  So there are two brothers who are
 fairly proximate.  Now, [Fonso] was not brought up, as a child, in our family, but with my uncle\rquote 
s family.  So when I lived with my uncle, for example, I got to know him very well, so he and I were very close.  And indeed, in terms of riding of horses, mules, donkeys, swimming, it was he who taught me these.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4151349\charrsid7427796 
