s first family, joined the military.  Then I didn\rquote t hear anything of him for a long while.  As a youngster, he wasn\rquote 
t doing terribly well, so he joined the military, and it seemed to have taught him a lot of discipline.  The next I heard from him, at a family reunion last year, was that he had just finished a Master\rquote s at Warwick, and that he 
was going off to Oxford Brookes to do his doctorate!  Which is quite impressive!  But Lester\rquote s kids have done fairly well.  I think they\rquote ve all gone to university and getting on with life.  Zenus\rquote 
s kids are all in the United States, but one of them is in I
pswich. Then my youngest brother, who came after me, we went to the same schools.  We went to primary school together, in Camberwell, then to secondary school.  And he was trained as a schoolteacher and taught junior school for quite a number of years, fo
