 Bunyan, all of those were part of a background.  I think he, perhaps, detected that one could build something on that kind of context.  Certainly, when I went to university, for a year or two, I continued to communicate with him, and he always encouraged
 me to say, \'93Look, don\rquote t submit anything unless you feel that you\rquote ve done your best at it\'94
, which I departed from, obviously, as an undergraduate, particularly in the second year at university!  (LAUGHS)  But, and as I said, when I had my 50}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\super\insrsid4151349\charrsid7427796 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 
