m still in touch with, who came, and who I have profound respect for.  There was another teacher at Crawford, who, in terms of literature, from fairly early at secondary school, introduced me to a range of 
writers and poets, whom I still read.  They always encouraged me, \'93Look, if you enjoy a writer, buy the book, so you always have it\'94.  And I try to pass this on to kids now.  I still have books from school days, and I can go back to them.  And it
