\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4151349\charrsid7427796 Oh yes!  My mother would have preferred me to do something else, in other words, be a religious man, that sort of stupidity.  My father felt, and that\rquote s what he said to all of us, \'93
Do whatever you want to, provided you do something\'94.  And that, in my case, and my younger brother and sister, I suppose, was a useful set of advice, but for the older ones it wasn\rquote 
t.  Provided you were doing something, he was quite happy with that.  And in terms of a home, that was one thing, I suppose, we had, compared to a number of other kids around us.  Certainly a number of white working-class kids, I realised that they didn
\rquote t have that kind of facility.  That we had a home.  My parents owned a number of other houses, I never had to pay a penny.  Even after I was at university, I still had my room at home, and I would come home every so often, and
 my room was just there.  Also, a number of my good friends whom I introduced to the household, whether I was there or not, could also come home and use my room.  Then, in between universities, I taught at my old school for a year, which was a stroke of l
uck, because I didn\rquote t know what to do, quite, and I went back to my school to see some of the teachers, and they said, \'93Well, whilst you\rquote re thinking of what you want to do, why don\rquote 
t you come and teach, we have a post in history, come and teach for a year, and decide what you want to do\'94.  So I did that.  And the people who had taught me were all still there, and so it was home, in a sense \endash 
 and seeing home from a different perspective. Even so, in my own household, my parents never asked me for a penny.  I 
had my room there.  My friends came and used it.  There was always a meal, etc..  So apart from occasionally taking a present for my mother or something like that, nothing at all, even though I was now a working person.  And that\rquote s how it\rquote 
s always been in our household.  I think, now, my sons treat us in much the same way, actually!  (LAUGHS)
