\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4151349\charrsid7427796 So in a way you were going back to the childhood there [at The Homestead, Baginton, outside Coventry], weren\rquote t you.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4151349\charrsid7427796 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri113\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin113\lin1871\itap0\pararsid6571465 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid6571465\charrsid6571465 Harry:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4151349\charrsid7427796 In a sense, yes.  And I still stick to that very strongly, in the sense of \'93
real property", as the lawyers call it, of residence and terra firma where you can grow something.  Because I think we take our civilisation for granted, don\rquote t we, that it\rquote 
s there.  And a lot of it is, of course, fiction!  (LAUGHS)  It could evaporate like that.  And I certainly tried to impress on my kids, \'93Look, get your own premises to live. This is your home, you can always live here, don\rquote t go and 
give your money to someone else".  It\rquote s an investment as well.  "If you have a flat, and even if you don\rquote 
t need it for any length of time, at the end of the day, you can sell it, you can move on.  But, you know, you have somewhere which is your own\'94.  I think that\rquote 
s one thing my parents impressed on all of us, so all my brothers and their children, they nearly all - I can\rquote t think of any of them who have not, whenever they stepped out into the world to make a living, then quickly move into buying somewhere o
f their own.  And, in fact, my brother, George, his sons in Ipswich, a number of them own quite a number of houses, which they just rent.  It seems to come in our blood now, you buy somewhere and you keep it!  (LAUGHS)
