\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4151349\charrsid7427796 And were you encouraged to mix, as a child, or not?
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4151349\charrsid7427796 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri113\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin113\lin1871\itap0\pararsid6571465 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid6571465\charrsid6571465 Harry:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4151349\charrsid7427796 Yes.  Oh yes.  I mean, not in a positive way, saying, \'93You must\'94 or \'93You must not\'94, it was - I mean, I recall, for example, my mother making the joke, oh, a couple of times, saying, \'93
Oh, coming home today, after going shopping, I saw two beautiful girls.  You must marry one of them!\'94  They\rquote re talking about white girls, you know!  \'93You really must marry one\'94, one of 
us, certainly!  (LAUGHS)  But more seriously, however, when we came to teenage years, when I was in the sixth form, for example, and began to mix very much more, because the school I went to was an all boys\rquote 
 school, and I was very shy of girls, but beginning to go to sixth form parties and Debating Society to other schools, school plays with girls\rquote 
 schools, and meeting a lot of girls and so on, then I remember one or two of them coming home.  And on one occasion, it was two days after Christmas \endash  this would have been about 1966/67 - the whole household went very quiet.  I hadn\rquote 
t said anything that she would be coming home, she just came and we sat down and had a tea \'85
