e to meet him, but then Hugh was a baby, they kept him in quarantine, he was only three months, but they wanted him to take a powerful injection, yellow fever injection, and we wouldn\rquote 
t allow it, so we left.  And then I never went back until after he had died.  But her mother, whom I\rquote 
ve met, she was quite approving, and once children came, and they visited and so forth, there was no problem.  But he was a strange character, the father, because Olympia, the eldest child, the eldest daughter, she had married 
