 because I had the material with me, I hadn\rquote t written it up in Tanzania.  So
 I was partly doing that.  Secondly, I was collecting material on violence.  So until recently I had a lot of material, particularly newspaper cuttings on incidents and so forth, on violence.  I did a couple of interviews with some police officers, and th
e idea was to do a big thing on violence, and to try to understand violence in relationship to Jamaica.  Why, what struck me about violence in Jamaica was that it was all around you, but it didn\rquote t touch the middle-classes at all.  There\rquote 
