\rquote s difficult to p
enetrate that society, in many ways.  And most people would agree that I was one of those who, perhaps, was most successful in doing so, because I was well integrated in terms of the political leadership of the PNP, and the leadership of the University, a
nd so on.  Socially, we and our children were well-established in school, and had good friends, but I did feel that one was something of an outsider, much more than I \endash  paradoxically \endash 
