\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 Well, Robin, I think, is a great inspiration, myself and to a lot of others, and is a very helpful person.  His work is very accessible.  He\rquote 
s been a great enabler, a great person who has helped people in their careers.  He\rquote s certainly helped me, and I know of a number of others whom he\rquote s helped.  I don\rquote t know i
f you know Mel Thompson?  Mel, we employed in the Centre, and she was writing a Master\rquote 
s for history, and Robin looked at it and encouraged her to upgrade it to a doctorate, and gave her time, created space to help her, in that regard.  His own work: I think partly because he\rquote s worked in West Africa, he\rquote 
s worked in the Caribbean, he was, of course, here, and I think he has a wider perspective of things.  Always willing to help people in every way.  I have the greatest respect for Robin.  And there\rquote s somethi
ng about him which can be quite deceptive.  Because he\rquote s seemingly laid back sometimes, people might think, he doesn\rquote 
