\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 Well, sometimes I think so, because, Warwick, I think I would have been the first person who, who\rquote 
s black, whom they would have had at that level.  There have been a number of Asians, but even to now, I don\rquote t know if they\rquote ve appointed any.  Certainly the impression I always had from the academics \endash 
 not the academics so much, but the administrative leadership in the place \endash  was one of total disrespect.  One had to be psychologically strong, I feel, to withstand that.
