\f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 book, and the Lambeth book.  I looked at those very closely, and a couple of pieces that she had written on Barbados.  And although she didn\rquote t know the rest of the Caribbean, I thought, \'93
Well, I can supply that\'94.  So I felt that it was the making of a good team to bring together an important piece of work which relates to Britain, it would have a policy implication, which was beginning to become something important both for the RAE 
\endash  Research Assessment \endash  as well as for the ESRC.  And whilst, for a long time, we resisted, in academia \endash  and certainly at CRER we did \endash 
