 with them, and ask for volunteers.  So in those ways, then, I was able to access various groups.  I had some incredible discussions with them, where they would quiz me about the value of this kind of work.  \'93Why are you doing it?\'94
  What will they gain?  M
ary and I went to most of those, and then once we had Dwayne on board, we would take him along as well.  And these turned out to be like rigorous academic discussions, some of them.  When Dwayne joined us, it was particularly useful that he could bring in
 the experience from North America, because, you see, some Groups in this country \endash  Caribbean Groups, some Muslim Groups \endash 
