ve written on this".  So there are those kind of things, which you can cope with, and I think she can cope with too.  But I think what became more difficult to handle was the time factor, that I knew that I wasn\rquote 
t going to be able to make my part of the contribution.  I just felt it was right to say to her, \'93Look, go ahead and write what you can.  The material is such that I\rquote ll still be able to write from it and if, later on down the road it\rquote 
