\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 Is Neil working at the moment?
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11671488 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri113\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin113\lin1871\itap0\pararsid9575211 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid6571465\charrsid6571465 Harry:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 Yes, he\rquote s into his second year of work now, in Hampstead, at the Royal Free, yeah.  He wants to be a general practitioner, rather than a specialist, because he feels again, it\rquote s because 
his overriding interest is politics, so he\rquote s really active - well, he was, not so much in the last two years, in the Labour Party and the Fabian Society, and he\rquote 
s involved with some Housing Associations, mentoring and so forth.  And so is Hugh.  Hugh\rquote s not interested in the national political scene, as in the local, and he\rquote 
s a governor at a school in one of the very deprived areas of East London, I think Walthamstow, and he gets himself involved in a lot of, of such activities.  His other interest is, of co
urse, organising golf tournaments!  (LAUGHS)  So he has an interest in these elite things!  But at the other end, I\rquote m pleased that both have a very good strong social consciences.  I think, if I\rquote ve failed them in any way, they don\rquote 
t put it in that way.  They simply say, \'93Look\'94, I\rquote ve brought them up in a context where they\rquote ve always been in a minority \endash  the schools they\rquote ve gone to, where they lived, they were the only blacks.  At Henry\rquote 
s, I think there were no more than two other black kids there.  There were a number of Asian kids, but not black kids.  I said, \'93Well, you know, that\rquote s not significantly different from when I was at school.  You can cope, you can get on with it
\'94.  And I think that gives them inner strength to survive wherever they are, and whatever context they\rquote 
re in. Neil speaks, or can speak, fluent Jamaican.  So can Hugh sometimes, because they listen carefully to things, and they can pick that up.  So sometimes, when Neil\rquote s here, we\rquote ll simply speak in Jamaican and so on, and they can mimic a
 number of our Jamaican friends perfectly!  But they\rquote 
re educated in classical music much more than in any other tradition, but as young people, they, themselves, have gone on, as any other young people would do, to be familiar with popular music and so on.  They\rquote 
re not as well read in black literature, or in literature \endash  well, Hugh is, in the Classics \endash  but as much as I would have liked to see them.  I\rquote 
m very happy to see that now, Neil, who needs to keep his mind active, because medicine doesn\rquote t seem to do that, that he\rquote s reading a lot of classics, and he reads a lot around current issues, in terms of politics and so forth.  
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11671488 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri113\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin113\lin1871\itap0\pararsid6571465 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid6571465\charrsid6571465 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 Can they cook Jamaican food?
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11671488 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri113\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin113\lin1871\itap0\pararsid9575211 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid6571465\charrsid6571465 Harry:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 Well, perhaps not so much Jamaican, but they can cook a wide range of things.  Hugh is proud to say that he \endash  and we\rquote ve seen an example of this \endash 
 that he can rustle up a meal for up to 25 people, very easily, of an evening.  And when for our 25}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\super\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796  anniversary, we were in Berlin, for the weekend, and we thought, \'93We\rquote ll go down to Bologna to visit him\'94
, and to our surprise, he put on an evening for us, and the flat he was sharing was choc-a-bloc, and he had done all the cooking!  And it was quite impressive!  And he puts on a lot of dinner parties from time to time.  I think it\rquote 
s because, like in my household, perhaps because we were nearly all boys, there\rquote s nothing in the household that we were not taught to do \endash  sewing, ironing \endash 
 in this household, I do all the ironing, Neil sometimes will do some.  Sewing, Neil and Selina will do.  If we are all here, and we are doing different things, anyone can cook, and there\rquote s nothing that I can\rquote t do.  Neil is the family
\rquote s carpenter, he bought himself a flat whilst he was here with us, in Kennington, and he ripped it inside out and re-did the plumbing, the carpentry, the electricity, everything, and sold it, and made, I think he said something like \'a3
26,000 for his labours, as a deposit for the flat he has bought up in Hampstead.  It\rquote s a sense which we have tried to put to them, that there should be nothing that you can\rquote 
t put your hand to, and you might not do it well at first, but you soon learn how to.  And when we were in India recently, I was saying this to one of Selina\rquote s nephews, as you know, in Indian families, boys are spoilt rotten, and we were cleaning
 a part of the yard, whilst we were there, which is outrageous that we, as visitors, and part of that family, should be doing what the servants usually do.  And I had the occasion talking, and I said, \'93
Well, you know, one of the things you should take as a
 principle of life is that anything that people who are socially inferior to you, or different from you, can do, you should be able to do, but only better.  It may well be that you choose not to do them, but you should be able to do them\'94.  I think it
\rquote s because we\rquote re peasants.  We come from that background where you do things, you may well choose not to, but it\rquote s not because you can\rquote t.  One of Neil\rquote 
s form of relaxation used to be to do knitting, and his girl friend, who come to the house, she basically thou
ght him utterly crazy!  (LAUGHS)  He used to be very upset at school when his teachers - he said they were very discriminating, because they would associate certain activities with girls, which he could do better than they could!  (LAUGHS)  So I\rquote 
m very proud in that regard, that they are well balanced people.  \tab The only thing I\rquote m, you know, as I say, in terms of their music, and I think they\rquote ll come back to it, this piano here, for example, which, I don\rquote t know if I
\rquote ve told you the story of it?  Neil\rquote s piano teacher thought he was of outstanding ability.  The Arts Council, each year will give a grant \endash  one to an institution, one to an individual - 
