\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri113\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin113\lin1871\itap0\pararsid9575211 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid6571465\charrsid6571465 Harry:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 And, they put Neil in for it and he, he won one.  He won this.  And what the schema is, the scheme is, is that if you buy an instrument you pay 50 per cent, and they pay 50 per cent.  And if it\rquote 
s over 20, they pay something like 60 per cent.  So we ask him whether he wanted a violin or flute, because he\rquote s done all of these up to Grade 8, and the Diploma in the piano as well - which one did he want?  He said, \'93A piano\'94
.  So we came to London to this warehouse, not far from here in Lewisham, it\rquote s vast!  It just goes on and on.  This was one of the cheaper ones, I think we paid \'a310,000!  I thought, \'93We could afford five, and they put five in\'94
.  So, technically, it\rquote s his.  But we said, when he has a daughter, we\rquote ll make sure she enjoys music and she can have it, or whoever has a daughter first!  But he\rquote 
s a brilliant pianist, flautist and violinist, in all three, and when he was a chorister, he did quite a lot of solos, and got royalties from it!  And there are some friends of ours who were out in Australia, and we had a call from them once, and they
\rquote re saying, one day, saying they\rquote ve just seen Neil on television!  (LAUGHS)  You know that programme }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 Songs of Praise}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 , comes out on a Sunday, well, when he was a chorister he appeared in that quite a bit.  (LAUGHS)   But
 no, Neil is a person, we feel the danger with him is that he has too many abilities, that whatever he puts his hand or his mind to, he does brilliantly.  I\rquote 
ve known a number of people like that who, in the end, they end up not doing very much.  They end u
p not doing very much, because nothing, for them, is that difficult or hard, like for me,!  (LAUGHS)  Even so, in discussions with Selina, I always say that I still feel that perhaps Hugh is the more brilliant, but it doesn\rquote 
t come out in the same way. Hugh did five \lquote A\rquote  levels, and he, I think he only got two A\rquote s, and the rest were B\rquote 
s, and Neil always treat him as a bit of a dumbo, you know!  But when it comes to his courage and his sense of adventure \endash  Neil has that as well - I mean, for example, he went f
rom Coventry, overland to India, and he was passing through some really dangerous places, and he did it well.  He wanted to go from door to door, from Coventry, by bus, overland, to Goa, to his grandmother\rquote 
s.  And did it.  But Hugh, his courage, when he went to Italy, where he had to sort out everything for himself, and the language was new to him, he took a course of three months or something, went there, got himself into a local Club.  Because he said, 
\'93Look, to get into Italian," he realised that to get into it, if he stayed with the English kids, as they all were doing, those who were there from Britain, \'93They all stuck together\'94, he said, \'93The first thing to do is to get away from that.
\'94  So he\rquote d meet them once a week, for a drink.  But he joined a local football club, where they just treated him as anyone else, and so he had to cope.  Since he\rquote s keen at sports, things that we\rquote 
ve never made any attempt to help him with, like skiing and organising these, and he does all of those things himself, and he\rquote s just a wise person.  You know some people and you feel their judgement and things is so balanced, and he\rquote 
s a very balanced, wise and courageous person.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11671488 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 
