\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 It is rather!  But, again, when I speak to young black people in London nowadays, place is important for them, in t
erms of their friendships, and with Hugh and Neil as well.  Neil wants to be in Hampstead because most of his friends are around there.  Where he\rquote 
s bought his flat, I think four, four of his friends from Cambridge live around there.  Hugh, in Hoxton, he was saying he\rquote s got about three or four friends or more, in that area as well.  For us, that\rquote 
s never been important, living where your friends are.  I think it\rquote s perhaps that fractured, fragmented kind of lives that we\rquote ve lived in different places, and you don\rquote t see your friendship as being restricted to a place.  I\rquote 
m looking very much forward to two weeks\rquote  time, some old friends from Tanzania days visiting from, from Boston.  He\rquote s a medic who teaches and works at Harvard.  She\rquote s a lawyer who practices in, in
 Boston.  Now, Selina was remarking that she\rquote s not seen either of them for 25 years, when we last, as a family, four of us, stayed with them in Boston.  But I\rquote ve seen them several times, because I\rquote 
ve been to Boston several times, and just stay with them, passing through.  Hugh has been and visited with a cohort of friends and so on.  But, we\rquote 
re always in touch and so on, and we regard them as very dear friends, from Tanzania days.  Then whilst we were in India, we had a call from a friend who was visiting from Jamaica, who was the Ambassador to Washington \endash  Jamaica\rquote 
s Ambassador to Washington \endash  whom, when he comes to Britain from time to time, we see each other.  When he was in Washington, we just visited him once there, and we were doing a tour of the US, se
eing people at different places, and when we got there, he apologised, said he has got to go to the airport immediately, to meet the Prime Minister, because he\rquote s, the Prime Minister\rquote 
s daughter was graduating somewhere else in the States, and he had a call, that same day, that obviously, he\rquote 
s got to go and meet his Prime Minister!  (LAUGHS)  Not only that, the Prime Minister wanted him to accompany, both he and his wife, to meet his daughter.  Of course, as Ambassador, you can\rquote t say no, can you!  So although
 we went to see them, and we were staying a couple of nights, we had the house to ourselves, with their servants, swimming pool, everything, but not them!  I think we have some very firm, good, long-standing friends in that way.  When one of them died, re
cently, in Arizona, we went for the funeral.  We just stopped everything and went.  Friends from elsewhere turned up as well for that.  What I\rquote m saying is that I sometimes think, in terms of when we\rquote 
re really old and grey, in terms of having friends nearby, we will not be, and that may be something to reflect on and think about.
