\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 That\rquote s right.  Precisely!  Even that, alone, requires some resources, doesn\rquote 
t it?  And I think, as people are able to see to themselves, for their own personal physical needs, then the need becomes less, in instrumental terms, to maintain that relationship.  I 
have two friends, in particular, two women who, from early in their lives, decided they would not have children.  One of them had a sister, and that sister died, fortunately that sister had a daughter.  But in terms of her family, that\rquote 
s it.  She doesn\rquote t have any blood relatives. The other person \endash  and that one is American.  The other person is an Englishwoman.  She said she had an auntie, apart from her parents, and that\rquote s all the blood line she knew of.  They
\rquote re both now dead, well, they\rquote ve been dead for 
some time, so she has no children, and both of them decided from early in life, they would have been in their, in their thirties, not to have children, to tie their wombs or something, and that they wouldn\rquote 
t have children at all.  Now, what gives them the confidence, or the stability to do that sort of thing?  I suspect is that financially, they\rquote 
re well-heeled people, they can always buy in certain services.  I suppose what would be missing is the emotional factor, but friendship and other things can, can counter that, I suspect.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid9575211  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 So it\rquote 
s rather sad in that regard, certainly in our family, I have no illusions that the close bonding that exists now between, say, myself and some of my brothers, between Selina, myself and her brothers, and all of her sisters, ap
art from one!  But even the one where she\rquote s a troublemaker, it\rquote s a bond of some kind, isn\rquote t it?  But in the next generation, it won\rquote t be, I don\rquote t think.  Whether that is true of most families or not, I don\rquote 
t know.  Do you feel that your children will be in touch with \'85 ?
