\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11671488\charrsid7427796 Oh, gosh!  That\rquote s, that\rquote s very difficult indeed.  The worst?  Okay, let\rquote s say the best.  The best.  I think the best thing is having two sons, or children, I\rquote 
m not particular that they should be sons.  If they had been daughters, they\rquote d have been equally - in fact, I wanted one to have been a daughter!  Having kids whom I\rquote ve been able to bring up in a way that they\rquote 
re our friends, and that, in a way, I wasn\rquote t brought up quite that way, though I had a nice teasing relationship with my parents, but in a way that they have a strong sen
se of responsibility for themselves and for people, and a sense of society.  And whether it comes from us, I don\rquote 
t know, but perhaps it has, or perhaps not, but that they have a conscience.  I think that is the proudest thing I can, I can think of. 
